.TH "of_gpio_simple_xlate" 9 "of_gpio_simple_xlate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_gpio_simple_xlate \- translate gpiospec to the GPIO number and flags
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_gpio_simple_xlate
.BI "(struct gpio_chip *gc "  ","
.BI "const struct of_phandle_args *gpiospec "  ","
.BI "u32 *flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gc" 12
pointer to the gpio_chip structure
.IP "gpiospec" 12
GPIO specifier as found in the device tree
.IP "flags" 12
a flags pointer to fill in
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is simple translation function, suitable for the most 1:1 mapped
GPIO chips. This function performs only one sanity check: whether GPIO
is less than ngpios (that is specified in the gpio_chip).
